# TypeScript Standards

## Types
- All shared types in `types/index.ts` — no inline type definitions for domain models
- Agent-specific types (e.g. `TeamPhaseInfo`, `RoleSegment`) co-located in their module
- Prefer `type` over `interface` for data shapes; use `interface` only for contracts agents/providers implement
- No `any` — use `unknown` + type narrowing when type is uncertain

## Code Style
- Named exports only — no default exports (except Next.js pages)
- Async generators for streaming: `async *method(): AsyncIterable<string>`
- Functional components with explicit prop interfaces
- Destructure props in function signature, not in body
- No barrel files (`index.ts` re-exports) except for `lib/storage/index.ts` facade

## Error Handling
- LLM errors: catch, log server-side, surface user-friendly message via `[ERROR: ...]` in stream
- Never swallow errors silently — at minimum `console.error` with context
- API routes: return structured JSON errors with appropriate status codes

## Naming
- Files: kebab-case (`sprint-orchestrator.ts`)
- Components: PascalCase (`MessageBubble.tsx`)
- Hooks: camelCase with `use` prefix (`useChat.ts`)
- Types: PascalCase (`ChatMessage`, `SprintContext`)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE for module-level (`MAX_QA_RETRIES`, `PROMPT_BA`)
